Subject: RE: BusDepot.Com Beta Test - STILL TESTING

The BusDepot.com beta test will continue overnight, as I have had so
much help from list members that I am not done fixing everything! (I
prefer to look at it this way, rather than from the negative standpoint
of their being so much to fix. :-)  New "hoped for" live date is
sometime tomorrow - maybe.  I'd rather be cautious than jump the gun.

I have implemented many suggestions made by people who sent comments,
and have some to do still. The site will definitely be easier for you to
use and more accurate, directly as a result of your input.  So keep
sending your comments, bug reports, etc. You are directly influencing
the look/feel of the site in a big way (and are finding plenty of stupid
part errors, too, which is great). Everything helps. 

I have copied the section of my original email regarding the beta test,
below, explaining some of what I'm looking for. Please go all the way to
placing an "order" if you can. (It will not be filled if placed while we
are beta-testing, but it will help us make sure everything works.) Also
we have had isolated complaints about people being unable to set up an
account, shopping cart abnormalities, and the checkout form adding up
the prices plus shipping incorrectly. (!)  Let me know if any of these
happen to you.  And please provide as much detail as possible, i.e. what
page you were on, what browser, if you got an error message what it
said, etc.

I will continue my offer to send a 10% off coupon to anyone who sends me
a bonafide list of bugs, errors, problems, etc. (I'll send it after this
is over, in a few days or so.)

Once again, the test URL is  http://venus.webappcabaret.net/busdepot   .
I will post here when the site goes live and the testing is over.

Thanks again for all your help. You're all great!!!  

- Ron Salmon
  The Bus Depot, Inc.
